{"chunk_id": "440a4bca-f834-440d-8eba-d4c91c4e7a8e", "source_database": "ICMR", "document_title": "ICMR_NIN_Dietary_Guidelines_Real.pdf", "publication_version": "Latest", "chunk_sequence_number": 82, "content_type": "Medical Guideline", "language": "English", "text": "it increases susceptibility to infection and impairs learning ability. /c63Plant foods like green leafy vegetables, legumes and dry fruits contain iron. /c63Iron is also obtained through meat, fish and poultry products. /c63Iron bio-availability is poor from plant foods but is good from animal foods. /c63Vitamin C - rich fruits like gooseberries (Amla), guava and citrus improve iron absorption from plant foods. /c63Beverages like tea bind dietary iron and make it unavailable. Hence, they should be avoided before during or soon after a meal. /c63Commonly consumed plant based diets provide around 18mg of iron as against recommended intake of 35mg per day. Therefore, supplementation of iron (100 mg elemental iron, 0.5 mg folic acid) is recommended for 100 days during th pregnancy from 16 week", "embedding": [-0.002886102069169283, -0.007204165682196617, -0.07312357425689697, 0.13652783632278442, 0.07292298227548599, 0.07354027777910233, -0.01744120568037033, 0.02953167073428631, -0.05095415934920311, -0.04773468151688576, -0.02887461893260479, -0.008740599267184734, -0.08598688244819641, -0.0839933231472969, -0.018764786422252655, -0.005330842919647694, 0.08620288968086243, 0.018610699102282524, -0.03891431540250778, 0.013187375850975513, -0.07628636062145233, 0.0033624961506575346, 0.06072118878364563, -0.0406048521399498, 0.002296935301274061, -0.01622290536761284, 0.04406450316309929, 0.0114516606554389, -0.03828687220811844, 0.05737403407692909, -0.04540259763598442, 0.03940706327557564, -0.008835921064019203, 0.03197520598769188, -0.12749825417995453, 0.04142506793141365, -0.009460466913878918, -0.13104932010173798, -0.017020156607031822, -0.02060449868440628, -0.007523076143115759, 0.041039705276489